Jaundice:

• Jaundice is a common liver disorder

Symptoms to look for:

• Yellowing of skin, eyes, tongue and urine
• Weakness
• Headaches
• Fever
• Loss of appetite
• Severe constipation
• Nausea
• Pain around the liver

Causes:

• Presence of excessive bile acids, a digestive acid produced in the liver, in the blood
• Blockage of bile ducts due to:
   o Gallstones
   o Hepatitis
   o Other reasons
• Some diseases which block the bile duct include:
   o Haemolytic anaemia
   o Typhoid
   o Malaria
   o Yellow fever
   o Tuberculosis

